==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Partiality
<hw>Par`ti*al"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?; 277)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>partialit⟦eacute⟧</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The quality or
state of being partial; inclination to favor one party, or one side of a
question, more than the other; undue bias of mind.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A predilection or inclination to one thing rather
than to others; special taste or liking; <as>as, a <ex>partiality</ex>
for poetry or painting</as>.</def> <rj><au>Roget.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Partialize</ent>⟦br⟧
